    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-30T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-30T10:00:00-05:00" n="521"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Bolivia/152: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-30T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 30, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:28 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>280. Department’s 238, April 27, 8 p.m. Argentines have already bought at least
                    175 tons of rubber. Shipments are now being made by air to Cochabamba taking
                    advantage of low LAB<note n="5" xml:id="d521fn5">Lloyd Aéreo Boliviano.</note>
                    freight rate and thence by rail to Buenos Aires. Price of recent market reported
                    reliably to have been 56 cents per pound c.i.f. Buenos Aires which works out
                    about 48 cents f.o.b. Beni.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
